Reference Cone of Vision used for all Spectators. This is equivalent to the curve generated from the intersection of the near clipping plane and the viewing frustum.It should be planar and closed and in a plane parallel to the global XY Plane.Default value is a square based frustum with 30 degree field of view and near clipping plane 0.1 from the eye reference location. Giving a a 0.115 * 0.115 square EffectiveConeOfVision.
A curve consisting of a continuous chain of straight line segments. The Polyline is considered closed if the first and last ControlPoints are coincident
Optional focal point to set the view direction of the spectators. If none provided the Avalue is calculated using the neutral viewing direction of each spectator.
Defines a dimensionless location in three-dimensional space.
Activity area projected to the spectator's viewing plane.
Resulting Polyline after clipping the full activity area with the cone of vision.
Effective cone of vision orientated to the spectator.
Point representing the spectator's singular eye reference.
Interface for Results belonging to a particular object. The owning object is identified and correlated to the Results by its ID.

Base interface for all analytical results.
For expanded functionality, a result class should generally either implement the IResultItem or IResultCollection interface, or one of their sub-interfaces, rather than this interface directly.
Interface for results that correspond to a particular case.
Interface for results that correspond to a particular time step, for example a discrete result from a time history anlysis.

A straight segment in space defining the shortest distance between two points in three-dimensional Euclidean geometry.
The Vector from Start to End defines the Line direction, which can be important for some applications.
Defines a direction and magnitude in three-dimensional Euclidean space.
